# Repository scope (AI-QA reference)

This project prioritizes **repeatable QA guidance** over shipping Playwright code in every change.

## Default scope

- Edit only under `wiki/`, `.cursor/skills/`, `.cursor/agents/`, and `.cursor/rules/` unless the user explicitly asks to change application or test code.
- Treat `wiki/assignment.md` and `wiki/requirements.md` as **requirements references** — do not duplicate their full text unnecessarily; link and summarize.

## When automation is in scope

- If the user explicitly requests Playwright/tests or `playwright.config.ts` changes, follow `.cursor/agents/developer.md` (branch policy, skills) and keep diffs small.

## AI-in-QA stance

- Use **skills** for structured test design and code-quality patterns.
- Prefer **MCP browser** for exploration and evidence; **committed tests** are for regression only when the user wants them implemented.
